<p>I am using VBA code to generate an email via Excel. When I run my code it automatically takes Times Roman font for mail body whereas my Outlook has Calibri as default font.</p>  <p>I want to have Calibri as my mail body font and I don't want to hardcode it.</p>  <p>Here is my code:</p>  <pre><code> '-------------Setting Body &amp; Body Format --------------------------             .BodyFormat = 2 '1=Plain text, 2=olFormatHTML 3=RichText             .BodyFormat = olFormatHTML             .body = StartBody &amp; vbNewLine &amp; vbNewLine &amp; BodyVal &amp; vbNewLine &amp; vbCrLf             ' .HTMLBody = " &lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt; " &amp; BodyVal &amp; " &lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt; "   '---for reference if needed in future for html body setting          '-------If preview button checked email will be displayed else it will be send to the reciepient         If (preview = True) Then             .Display         Else             '.HTMLBody = StartBody &amp; " &lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt; " &amp; BodyVal &amp; " &lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt; " &amp; OutMail.HTMLBody             .Display             .Send             '.Save         End If     End With     On Error GoTo 0     Set OutMail = Nothing     Set OutApp = Nothing End Sub </code></pre>